        <definition>Tensor cytnx::algo::Vstack</definition>
        <argsstring>(const std::vector&lt; Tensor &gt; &amp;In_tensors)</argsstring>
        <name>Vstack</name>
        <qualifiedname>cytnx::algo::Vstack</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>const std::vector&lt; <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref> &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>In_tensors</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>vertical stack a list of <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function will stack vertically a list of Matrices (a 2d tensor) with same number of columns. That is, if the input Matrices are <formula id="0">$ [M_1, M_2, M_3] $</formula>, the output will be:  <formula id="1">\[
\begin{bmatrix}
M_1\\
M_2\\
M_3\\
\end{bmatrix}
\]</formula> Note that the number of columns of <formula id="2">$ M_1 $</formula>, <formula id="3">$ M_2 $</formula> and <formula id="4">$ M_3 $</formula> should be the same. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">In_tensors</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a list of 2d <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref> (Matrix). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>[<ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref>] return a new <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref> that is the vertical stack of <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput> cannot be empty.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput> need to be 2d <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref> (Matrix).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput> should have same number of columns.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput> should be on same device.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The data type of the input <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput> cannot be Type.Bool or Type.Void. (see cytnx::Type) </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>If the data type of the input <computeroutput>In_tensors</computeroutput> are different, the data type of the output <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref> will be the stronger one. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
