        <briefdescription>
<para>split a Matrix (a 2d <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref>) into a list of Matrices along the vertical direction. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function will split a Matrix (a 2d <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref>) into a list of Matrices along the vertical direction. That is, if the input Matrix <computeroutput>Tin</computeroutput> is:  <formula id="6">\[
M = \begin{bmatrix}
m_{11} &amp; m_{12} &amp; m_{13}\\
m_{21} &amp; m_{22} &amp; m_{23}\\
m_{31} &amp; m_{32} &amp; m_{33}\\
\end{bmatrix}
\]</formula> and the input <computeroutput>dims</computeroutput> is <formula id="7">$ [1,2] $</formula>, the output will be <formula id="8">$ [M_1, M_2] $</formula>, where:  <formula id="9">\[
M_1 = \begin{bmatrix}
m_{11} &amp; m_{12} &amp; m_{13}\\
\end{bmatrix}
\]</formula> and  <formula id="10">\[
M_2 = \begin{bmatrix}
m_{21} &amp; m_{22} &amp; m_{23}\\
m_{31} &amp; m_{32} &amp; m_{33}\\
\end{bmatrix}
\]</formula></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">Tin</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the input Matrix (a 2d <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref>). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">dims</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the row number of each Matrix in the output list. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>[std::vector&lt;Tensor&gt;] return a list of Matrices that is the split of <computeroutput>Tin</computeroutput> with respect to <computeroutput>dims</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>Tin</computeroutput> need to be 2d <ref refid="classcytnx_1_1Tensor" kindref="compound">Tensor</ref> (Matrix).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>dims</computeroutput> cannot be empty.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The input <computeroutput>dims</computeroutput> cannot be out of range. That is, the summation of <computeroutput>dims</computeroutput> need equal to the number of rows of <computeroutput>Tin</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The elements in <computeroutput>dims</computeroutput> cannot be zero. </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="namespacecytnx_1_1algo_1a882e6a0d33e659d35f7f1df18a51152a" kindref="member">Hsplit</ref>, <ref refid="namespacecytnx_1_1algo_1a993ff4c266490e7fee38ab2f20e6aa50" kindref="member">Vstack</ref> </para>
